  "description": "PsiConnect is a large-scale multimodal neuroimaging study investigating context-dependent neural and subjective effects of psilocybin in 62 participants. The dataset combines functional, structural, and diffusion-weighted MRI with concurrent EEG acquired before and after psilocybin administration (19 mg), incorporating resting-state and naturalistic conditions (guided meditation, music listening, movie watching). Half the cohort completed 8-week meditation training, enabling investigation of interactions between meditation, psilocybin, and brain function. Comprehensive behavioral and self-report measures capture acute and longitudinal cognitive and subjective effects with follow-ups to one year post-administration.",
  "methods_description": "Multimodal neuroimaging acquisition including multi-echo fMRI (enhanced signal-to-noise ratio and reduced susceptibility artifacts), structural MRI, diffusion-weighted imaging, and concurrent EEG. Study design includes resting-state scans and three naturalistic conditions: guided meditation, music listening, and movie watching. Behavioral and self-report measures were collected acutely and longitudinally through one-year follow-up.",
